data.title: David Fisher, Basketball Player

data.text:
David Fisher - Points

David Fisher scores a career high 25 points (2006)

On February 02, 2006, David Fisher set his career high in points in a NCAA game. That day he scored 25 points in New Mexico State Aggies's home win against Utah State Aggies, 93-86. He also had 7 rebounds, 3 assists, 2 steals. He shot 12/15 from two, shooting at 80.0% from the field. He also shot 1/1 from the free-throw line.

David Fisher - Rebounds

David Fisher grabs a career high 12 rebounds (2006)

On February 11, 2006, David Fisher set his career high in rebounds in a NCAA game. That day he grabbed 12 rebounds in New Mexico State Aggies's road win against Utah State Aggies, 77-83. He also had 13 points, 1 assist and 1 block.

David Fisher - Assists

David Fisher gives a career high 3 assists (2006)

On February 18, 2006, David Fisher tied his career high in assists in a NCAA game. That day he dished 3 assists in New Mexico State Aggies's road win against Pacific Tigers, 69-79. He also had 13 points, 9 rebounds, 2 steals.

David Fisher - Steals

David Fisher has a career high 3 steals (2006)

On February 15, 2006, David Fisher set his career high in steals in a NCAA game. That day he reached 3 steals in New Mexico State Aggies's home win against Boise State Broncos, 73-68. He also had 5 points, 8 rebounds.

David Fisher - Blocks

David Fisher blocks a career high 4 shots (2005)

On November 26, 2005, David Fisher set his career high in blocks in a NCAA game. That day he went for 4 blocks in New Mexico State Aggies's home loss against Sam Houston State Bearkats, 77-78. He also had 5 points, 7 rebounds.

David Fisher - Efficiency

David Fisher records a career high 32 efficiency rating (2006)

On February 02, 2006, David Fisher set his career high in efficiency in a NCAA game. That day he accomplished 32 efficiency in New Mexico State Aggies's home win against Utah State Aggies, 93-86. He also had 25 points, 7 rebounds and 3 assists.
